data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync calls will throw at runtime — with no opt-in to restore the old behavior.**

In EF Core 10, the Cosmos DB provider let you opt into sync-over-async. In EF Core 11, that opt-in is **removed entirely**. Any synchronous I/O call (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) **always throws**.

### Fix: convert everything to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

You'll also need to update all callers to `await` these methods and propagate `async` up the call chain. The Cosmos DB SDK is async-only, so there's no workaround — this is a permanent change.
